name: wood preservation facility construction, flow coating equipment | wood preservation facility, flow coating equipment | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/11509/documentation

Flow coating is an automated method of applying industrial liquid coatings that involves directing numerous individual streams of coating over one or multiple parts that move horizontally on a conveyor. Flow coating can be used to cover multi-dimensional surfaces of a variety of shapes. The run-off paint or wood preserverative is recollected and reused.;The dataset represents a modern flow coating equipment with a estimated througput of about window frames per hour and an estimated service life of 20 years (according to producer information.

Infrastructure dataset containing the main elements of the facility.

Material (production and disposal) needed for a flow coating equipment, e.g. used for wood preservation in windows production. Maintenance is disregarded
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/429:Construction of other civil engineering projects/4290:Construction of other civil engineering projects

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from Germany and Switzerland. Location of plant within Europe of minor importance
